1.2:
God þat is good in him silf.  faire in hise aungelis. merveilouse|in hise seintis. and merciful vpon synners&meper; haue merci on vs now|& euer/ and &yogh;yue vs grace to holde þe weye of truþe&meper; in þise daies|of greet tribulacioun &Verbar; For now manye þat semeden to haue be|stable in vertu&meper; fallen from her holi purpose. dredyng losse of|worldli goodis & bodili peyne as Crist seiþ. Mat. xxiv o . 'Quoniam|habundabit iniquitas&meper; refrigescet caritas multorum' Vulg. Matt. xxiv. 12./ þat is to|seie.  þe greet plente and habundaunce of wickidnesse&meper; schal kele|or make coolde. þe charite of many. W. V. 'And for wickidness schal be plenteous, the charite of manye schal|wexe cold.' For now þe deuel haþ|marrid þis world&meper; bi his leeftenaunt anticrist þat men ben born|aboute in diuerse dou&yogh;tis&meper; as wawis of þe see/ wrechidli diuidid | in wonderful opyniouns&meper; iche nei&yogh;bore wiþ oþir &Verbar; But | Seint Poul|sett oon acorde&meper; in al cristendom & seiþ.  Eph. iv o . 'Vnus|dominus vna fides vnum baptisma' &Verbar; þat is to seie. þer is but oo|lord&meper; þat alle men schulden drede & loue/ oo feiþ&meper; þat alle men|schulden bileue wiþouten chaungyng/ oo baptem or cristendom&meper;|þat alle men schulden kepe wiþouten defouling &Verbar; Alas hou is þis|oonhed or vnite broken.  þat men vnrulid walken aftir her lustis.|as beestis in þe corne? certis þe wickid man þat Crist spekiþ of&meper;|haþ done þis dede/ Mat. xiii o . 'Inimicus homo superseminauit|zizaunia' Vulg. Matt. xiii. 25 'Inimicus eius superseminavit zizania'; but v. 28|'Inimicus homo hoc fecit.' &Verbar; Þat is to seie.  þe enemy of God haþ sowen taaris&meper;|vpon þe seed of Iesu Crist W. V. 'His enemy cam and sew above dernel (or cokil) in the midil of|whete.'  1388, 'His enemy cam and sewe above taris,' etc. &Verbar; Þis wickid man is anticrist&meper; þat|clowtiþ his lawis as roten raggis. to þe clene cloþ of Cristis gospel/|& wakiþ in malise as Iudas childe&meper; whilis Symon slepiþ & takiþ|noon hede &Verbar; O þou wickid man. is þer ony oþir þat may saue
 |soulis þan Crist Iesu?  God seiþ bi þe mouþe of Moyses.  Deuto.|xxxii o . 'percuciam & ego sanabo & non est qui de manu | mea |possit eruere' Vulg. Deut. xxxii. 39. &Verbar; þat is to seie.  I schal smyt & I schal heele&meper; &|þer is non þat mai skape fro myn hand W. V. 'I schal smyte & I schal heel, & there is not that fro myn hoond|may delyver.'  1388, 'I schale smyte, and I schal make hool; and noon is|that may delivere fro myn hond.' &Verbar; Who haþ þe keies of|Dauiþ to opyn heuene &yogh;atis&meper; & þanne noon oþir closiþ to close&meper;|& þanne noon oþir opyneþ? Seint Jon seiþ, Apoc. iii o . 'Sanctus &|verus habet clauem dauid qui aperit & nemo claudit. claudit &|nemo aperit' Vulg. Apoc. iii. 7 'Haec dicit Sanctus & Verus qui habet,' etc. &Verbar; Þat is to seie.  Holi & trewe Crist Iesu haþ þe|keie of Dauiþ þe whiche opineþ & noon oþir closiþ/ closiþ&meper; &|þanne noon oþir opineþ&meper;/ who dingeþ doun and þanne no man|reriþ/ who reriþ&meper; & þanne no man dingeþ doun.  Iob seiþ. xii o .|'Si destruxerit nemo est qui edificet&meper; si incluserit hominem nullus|est qui apariat' Vulg. Job xii. 14. &Verbar; Þat is to seie. whanne þe Lord God haþ distroied&meper;|þer may noon oþir bijlde/ & whanne þe Lord God stressiþ a man in þe|prisoun&meper; þer mai noon oþir delyuer him. ne quite him from hise|boondis W. V. 'If he destro&yogh;e, no man is that bilde up; if he inclose a man, no|man is that opene.'  1388, 'If he destrieth, no man is that bildith, if he|schitteth in a man, noon is that openeth.' &Verbar; And þerfore in þe vertu of þis name Iesu&meper; stondiþ al mannes|saluacioun/ as it is writen. Actus iv o . 'Nec enim aliud nomen est|sub celo datum hominibus vnde oporteat nos saluos fieri' Vulg. Act. iv. 12 'Nec enim aliud nomen est ... in quo,' etc. &Verbar; Seint|Petir seiþ. þer | is noon oþir name vndir heuene &yogh;yuen to men&meper; |but þis name Iesu. in þe whiche it bihoueþ vs to be made saaf/|for oonli in vertu of þis name&meper; comeþ remyssioun of synnes/ as it|is writen Luc. xxiiii o . 'Oportebat predicari in nomine eius penitenciam|& remissionem peccatorum in omnes gentes' Vulg. Luc. xxiv. 47. &Verbar; þat is to|seie.  It bihoued to be prechid among alle folkis&meper; penaunce &|remissioun of synnes in þe name of Iesu &Verbar; Art not þou þanne|a wickid man. a foultid schepard, a cruel beest. þe sone of perdicioun|& anticrist him silf. þat pretendist in þee & in þi membris|to bynde & lose. to blesse & curse. biside þis name Iesu?  Peple|wiþouten noumbre. folowyng þee & þi diuided lawis&meper; ben diuidid|from Crist Iesu/ & gon wiþ þee blyndlingis&meper; to helle for euere-more/
 |And þis is greetli to sorow. so ferforþe&meper; þat Crist makiþ|mornyng þervpon & seiþ. Ion v o . 'Ego veni in nomine patris mei|& non accepistis me&meper; si alius venerit in nomine eius illum | accipietis' Vulg. Joh. v. 43. &Verbar; þat is to seie. | I haue comen in þe name of my|fadir&meper; & &yogh;e haue not taken me/ whanne anoþir comeþ in his|owene name&meper; him &yogh;e schal take/ W. V. 'I cam in the name of my fadir, & &yogh;e token not me.  If another|schal come in his owne name, &yogh;e schulen receyve him.' And þis is anticrist as seint|Ion Crisostum seiþ vpon þis gospel. S. Ioan. Chrysostomus, Homilia XXVII in cap. Matt. xi (Opera, ed.|1547, tom. ii, col. 913). Mat. xi o .  'Tu es qui|venturus es an alium expectamus' Vulg. Matt. xi. 3. &Verbar; For who þat wole not|resceyue Crist&meper; in peyne of synne he is compellid & constreyned|to resceyue anticrist &Verbar;  Þerfore in þis tyme of hidouse derknes|somme seeken þe lanterne of li&yogh;t. of þe whiche spekiþ þe prophete.|Ps. cxviii. 'Lucerna pedibus meis verbum tuum' Vulg. Ps. cxviii. 105. &Verbar; þat is to seie.|Lord þi word is a lanterne to my feet. W. V. 'Lanterne to my feet thi woord.'  1388, 'Thi word is a lanterne|to my feet.' /  For as fer as þe li&yogh;t of þis|lanterne schineþ&meper; so fer derkness of synne & cloudis of þe fendis|temptaciouns vanischen awey & moun not abide/ And algatis|whanne þe lanterne li&yogh;tneþ into þe hert&meper; it purgeþ & clensiþ from|corrupcioun/ it swagiþ & heeliþ goostli soris/ As þe wise man|seiþ.  Sap. xvi o .  'Neque herba neque malagma sanauit illos&meper; | sed | omnipotens sermo tuus domine qui sanat vniuersa' Vulg. Sap. xvi. 12 'Neque herba neque malagma sanavit eos, sed tuus,|Domine, sermo qui sanat omnia.' &Verbar; þat is|to seie.  Neiþir herbe ne plaistir haþ helid hem&meper; but Lord þi|mi&yogh;ti word þat heeliþ alle þingis/ W. V. 'Forsothe neither erbe, ne plastre helde them; but thi word, Lord|that heleth all thingus.' For Lord whanne þou diedist|vpon þe cros&meper; þou puttidist in þi word þe spirit of lijf/ & &yogh;auest|to it power of quickenyng&meper; bi þin owene preciouse blood. as þou|þi silf seist.  Ion. vi o . 'verba que ego locutus sum vobis spiritus|& vita sunt' Vulg. Joh. vi. 64. &Verbar;  þat is to seie. þe wordis þat I speke to &yogh;ow&meper; þei|ben spirit & lijf &Verbar;

3.8:
Þe fifþe synne is envie&meper; of þi broþeris grace/ as whanne þi|nei&yogh;bour is wise. wel gouerned. preisid or born vp. riche. welþi.|strong. faire. or vertuouse in greet habundaunce of grace.  þanne|þis enviouse man.  sclaundriþ.  vpbreidiþ.  reproueþ.  dispisiþ.|hatiþ. & hyndriþ. scorneþ. & pursueþ.  to defoule & waast his|broþeris goodis þat ben goostli gracis&meper; as miche as he mai&meper;|as þe wise man seiþ &Verbar; Prou. xiiii o . 'Ambulans recto itinere|& timens deum. despicitur ab eo qui infami graditur via' Vulg. Prov. xiv. 2. &Verbar; | A man walking in | þe hi&yogh;e weie & dreding God&meper; is dispisid of|him þat walkiþ in þe wrong weye/ W. V. 'The goende in ri&yogh;t weie, & dredende God is dispised of hym that|goth in the evel losid weie.'  1388, 'A man goynge in ri&yogh;tful weie and dredinge|God, is dispisid of hym that goith in a weie of yuel fame.' whanne Iesu Crist kest|out a deuel&meper; from a man þat was doumb. as it is writen.  Mat.|xii o . Marc. iii o . Luc. xi o . Vulg. Matt. xii. 22; Marc. iii. 11, 12; Luc. xi. 14. anoon þis man bigan to speke: to|puplische þis miracle among þe peple/ Þanne scribis & pharises|enviouse sectis&meper; þat weren a fals priuat religioun/ sclaundrid þat|Crist wrou&yogh;t þis miracle&meper; in Belsabub þat was prince of deuelis &Verbar;
 |Belsabub is to seie a god of fli&yogh;es&meper; or ellis a god þat makiþ discorde/|Lord siþen þise sectis dursten seie&meper; þus to Crist heed of|mannis soule/ hou miche werre schullen þey moun dore seie&meper; to|hise hous-meyne?  Þus prelatis & freris in þise daies&meper; ben traueilid|wiþ þis synne a&yogh;en þe Holi Goost/ & schamfulli sclaundren her|symple briþeren&meper; þat casten yuel maners from her soule/ or|prechen þe gospel to Cristis entent&meper; to turne þe peple to vertuouse|lyuyng &Verbar;  Þei seien þis man haþ eten | a fli&yogh;e&meper; þat &yogh;yueþ him lore |of Goddis lawe/ þis is more foule to eete a flie&meper; þan to be a god|& chare þise fli&yogh;es/ Þus han þey brou&yogh;t her malice aboute&meper; to|sclaundir for Lollardis þat speken of God/ & dryuen þe peple|from þe feiþ&meper; þat durne not worche ne speke for sclaundir/ but|certis þey ben not worþi Crist&meper; þat stonyén for barkyng of þise|houndis/ for noon is worþi to be wiþ þis Lord&meper; þat schameþ his|seruyse in wel or in woo/ & suche men schewen hem traitours to|God&meper; þat wiþ her sclaundris hindren her briþeren/ & seyn þe|fende mai & wil&meper; make wise hise membris þat seruen him in|synne/ but so wole not Crist hise loued seruauntis&meper; þat lyuen in|clennes to serue him in vertu &Verbar; O I preie &yogh;ou&meper; who hard euer|a fouler blasfemye? certis þis dispit strecchiþ vnto þe godhed&meper; to|be punyschid in þe dai of iugement/ for Goddis lawe techiþ.|Prou. iii o .  'Noli prohibere benefacere qui potest si vales & ipse|benefac' Prov. iii. 27 'Noli prohibere benefacere eum qui potest,' etc. &Verbar;  Forbede him | not þat mai wel do&meper; but if þou mai do |wel þi silf W. V. 'Wile thou not forfenden hym that mai wel don, if thou maist, and|thiself wel do.'  1388, 'Nil thou forbede to do wel him that mai: if thou|maist, and do thou wel.' &Verbar; Þat a prest schulde not be lettid&meper; to preche þe|trouþe/ ne Goddis peple to speke of her bileue&meper; is opunli tau&yogh;t|in þe book of Numeri xi o . Vulg. Num. xi. 24-30. &Verbar; Þere it is rad&meper; þat Heldad & Medad|prophecied albeit þat þei weren not lisensid bi Moises &Verbar; Iosue þe|mynyster of Moises. and chosen of manye&meper; grucchiden a&yogh;ens þise|men. & mad his pleynt to Moises/ & Moises seide. whi art þou|enviouse for me? who mai werne þat alle þe peple prophecie. &|God graunt his spirit to hem? þis is confermed in þe gospel of|oure Lord Iesu Crist&meper; boþe in Mark ix o & in Luc. ix o .  'Magister|vidimus quemdam in nomine tuo demonia eicientem qui non|sequitur nos & prohibuimus eum/ Iesu autem ait/ Nolite prohibere
 |eum Vulg. Marc. ix. 37, 38. '&Verbar; Seint Ion euaungelist seide vnto Crist. Maister|we han sen a man casting out deuelis in þi name. þat sweþ not|vs&meper; & we han forboden him/ forsoþe Iesu seide.  Nile &yogh;e werne|him or forbeede him W. V. 'Maister, we sy&yogh;en sum oon for to caste out fendis in thi name,|the which sueth not us, and we han forbedun him.  Sothli Jhesus seith to|him, Nile &yogh;e forbede him.' &Verbar; Alas howe dorne oure bischopis for | schame&meper; offende | a&yogh;ens þise boþe Goddis lawes/ & docke her|prestis on euery side. to &yogh;yue hem a charge&meper; & priue hem þer|office &Verbar;  What is to be sett biforne þe bodi of Crist þat prestis|sacren? And siþen þei treten Cristis bodi. miche raþer seiþ Ierom|þei schullen preche & blesse Þe peple. Hec dist. 99 Gratian, Decreti Pars Prima, dist. xcv, cap. v (Migne, tom. 187,|col. 449). .  But here|þe enemyes of truþe obiectun & leyn for hem Poul&meper; where he seiþ|Ro. x o .  'Quomodo predicabunt nisi mittantur' Vulg. Rom. x. 15 'Quomodo vero praedicabunt,' etc. &Verbar;  How schullen|þei preche but if þei be sent?  wiþ þis þei blynden mani folk&meper;|kutting þe sentence from þe wordis/ for Poul meneþ þat prestis|schulde preche&meper; for þei ben sent/ boþe of God & of þe bischop&meper;|for to do þat office &Verbar;  And þe maister of sentence in his fourþe|book & þe XXIIII. dist. seiþ/ It is þe office of a deken&meper; to preche|þe gospel Petrus Lombardus, Sententiarum Libri IV , Lib. IV, dist. xxiv. 8|(Migne, tom. 191, col. 903). / þanne bi more strenger resoun&meper; it perteyneþ to a|prest/ For seint Ierom & seint Beede acorden togider & seyn/|Sicut in forma apostolorum est forma episcoporum&meper; ita in septuaginta|duobus discipulis est forma presbiterorum/ Ri&yogh;t as in þe|apostlis is þe forme of bischopis&meper; so in þre score & twelue disciplis. | is þe forme | of prestis/ But Crist &yogh;aue charge boþe to þise|bischopis & also to þise prestis&meper; & seide/ Mat. x o .  'Ecce ego|mitto vos' Vulg. Matt. x. 16. / & Luc. x o . 'Designauit Iesus alios septuaginta duos|& misit illos &c.;' Vulg. Luc. x. 1. &Verbar;  Loo I sende &yogh;ou as schepe among wolues &Verbar;|And efte Iesu asigned þrescore & twelue&meper; & sent hem to preche &Verbar;|How schal þise bischopis maynten þer constituciouns&meper; a&yogh;ens þer|God & holi seintis/ It schal be more suffurable to Sodom & Gomor&meper;|þan to þis peple þat disturblen Goddis ordinaunce &Verbar;

4.2:
But of þe greet cheef anticrist. þat passingli & in special maner|bringiþ forþ fals lawes a&yogh;ens Iesu Crist & pretendiþ him silf moost
 |hooli&meper; þus techiþ þe Lord God bi þe prophete Isaie ix o . 'Longeuus|& venerabilis ipse est caput. propheta docens mendacium. ipse est | cauda' Vulg. Isaias ix. 15 'Longaevus & honorabilis ipse est caput,' etc. &Verbar; A man of greet agee | & worschipful holden to þe|world&meper; he is heed and cheef anticrist/ a prophete or a prechour|techyng lesing&meper; he is þe taile of þis anticrist W. V. 'The longe lyvende and the w(o)rschepefull, he is the hed, and|the profete techende lesyng, he is the tail.'  1388, 'An elde man and onourable,|he is the heed, and a profete techynge a leesyng, he is the tail.' &Verbar; Of þis taile spekiþ|seint Petir more pleynli & seiþ. II. Pe. ii o . 'Fictis verbis in auaricia|de vobis negociabuntur' Vulg. 2 Pet. ii. 3. &Verbar; Þat is to seie. Þise ben goostli|marchauntis þat schal chaffare wiþ þe peple&meper; in feyned wordis W. V. 'And thei shulen marchaundise of &yogh;ou in coueitise bi feynyd wordis.'|1388, 'And thei schulen make marchaundie of &yogh;ou in coueytise bi feyned|wordis.' /|& wiþ her sweet likerouse speche&meper; þei bigilen þe hertis of innocentis.|for Iude seiþ. ii o . 'Mirantes personas hominum questus|causa' Vulg. Jud. 16 'Mirantes personas questus causa.' / Þat is to seie. þei schal worschip þe persoones of men&meper;|bicause of wynnyng &Verbar; Þis taile of anticrist schal not preche freeli|Thomas Alquin seiþ. li o . Vii o . ca. viii o but for 'mammona iniquitatis'/|þat is for coueitise. so ferforþe crueli a&yogh;enstonding þe prechours of|trouþe. þat þei schul be holden in þer daies as cursid of þe peple &Verbar;|And seint Ion euaungelist seiþ. Apoc. xiii o . 'Quod nemo emet neque|vendet nisi habuerit carecterem bestie' Vulg. Apoc. xiii. 17 'Et ne quis possit emere aut vendere nisi qui habet|characterem bestiae.' &Verbar; þer schal no man in | þat | tyme bie ne selle be he boond be he free. but if he haue þe|mark of þe beest. eiþer in his forhed or in his ri&yogh;t hond or ellis in|noumbre/ W. V. 'No man mai bye, or sille, no but thei that han the caracter, (or|lettre) or the name, or the noumbre of his name.'  1388, 'No man may bie,|ethir sille, but thei han the caracter, ether the name of the beest, ether the|noumbre of his name.' þat is to seie. þer schal no man preche Goddis word in|þoo daies neiþer heere it. but if he haue a special lettir of lisence|þat is clepid þe mark of þis beest anticrist/ or ellis þat þei maynten|bi word or bi dede. or in boþe. þat his lawe & his ordinaunce is|good & trewe/ & worþi to be holden of þe peple &Verbar; But it is ferful|þat folowiþ aftir.  Apoc. xiiii o . 'Si quis acceperit carecterem|bestie &c.;' Vulg. Apoc. xiv. 9. &Verbar; Seynt Ion seiþ. who þat euer worschipiþ þis beest
 |anticrist. & takiþ þis forseid mark&meper; he schal drink a drau&yogh;t of þe|wyn of Goddis wraþþe/ & he schal be turmentid in fire & brymston&meper;|in þe si&yogh;t of holi aungelis & in þe si&yogh;t of þe lombe/ & þe|smoke of her turmentrie. schal sti&yogh;e vp in to þe world of worldis&meper;|þat is wiþouten ende W. V. 'If ony man shal worschipe the beest, and the image of it, and take|the tokne in his forhed, or in his hand, & þis shal drinke of the wijn of Goddis|wrath ... and shal be tourmentid with fijr and brunston, in the si&yogh;t of holy|aungelis, and before the si&yogh;t of the lomb.  And the smoke of her tourmentis|shal sti&yogh;e up in to worldlis of worldlis.' &Verbar;

7.11:
Alle holi seyntis&meper; acorden in þis/ þat oure chirche material&meper;|þat is ordeyned for parischynes. where þei comen togidir/ | schal |be made wiþ vertuouse meenes&meper; & in an honest mesure/  But on|alwise it must be fled&meper; þat in þis chirche þer schewe no pride/|neiþir outtrage passingli&meper; ouer þe boundis of pouert/ neiþir in|stoon. tymber or leed&meper; neiþir in glasse. lyme or plaistir/ neiþir|in belle laump or li&yogh;t&meper; neiþir in chalise booke or vestment/ neiþir|in stepile seetis or peynting&meper; or oþir hournementis þat longen to|þis chirche/ & diligentli þis must be markid&meper; þat þei bowe to|pouerte/ to eschewe veyn glory of þis world&meper; & glorifie þe cros|of God/  But þis word of Cristis cros&meper; is foli to hem þat schal be|dampned/ þat tenten to signes as comune hooris&meper; & leesen þe
 |vertu of her soule &Verbar;  Poul comendiþ þe coming of Crist&meper; & þe lowe|meking in his manhed/ ii o Cor. viii o . 'Scitis enim gratiam domini|nostri Iesu Christi quoniam propter vos egenus factus est cum esset|diues in omnibus vt illius inopia vos diuites essetis' Vulg. 2 Cor. viii. 9 'Scitis enim gratiam domini nostri Iesu Christi|quoniam propter vos egenus factus est, cum esset dives, ut illius inopia vos|divites essetis.' &Verbar;  Forsoþe|&yogh;e owen for to knowe&meper; þe grace of oure Lord Iesu Crist/ for whanne|he was riche in alle þingis&meper; he was made pore in man for &yogh;ou/ | | þat &yogh;e schulden be riche in goostli þing&meper; þoru&yogh; þis vertuouse nede|in Crist W. V. 'Sothli &yogh;e witen the grace of oure Lorde Jhesu Christ, forwhi he|was made nedy for us, whanne he was ryche, that &yogh;e schulden be maad ryche|by his myseste (or nedynesse).' &Verbar; Crist þat blameþ alle viciouse meenes&meper; in þe seruyce|of hise peple/ wil not autorise it to him silf&meper; ne defend it in his|owene hous/ as seint Mathew seiþ. þe xxiiii o . Mar. xiii o . &|Luk. xxi o Matt. xxiv. 1, 2; Marc. xiii. 1, 2; Luc. xxi. 5, 6. / 'Egressus Iesu de templo ibat & accesserunt ad eum|discipuli eius ut ostenderent ei edificaciones templi. ipse autem|respondens dixit eis. videtis hec omnia/ amen dico vobis. non|relinquitur hic lapis super lapidem. qui non destruatur' &Verbar; Mathew|Mark & seint Luk. acorden togidir in þis oo sentence/ þat whanne|Iesu went out of þe temple&meper; þer nei&yogh;ed to him hise disciplis/ for|to schewe him þe bildyng þerof&meper; & þe curiouse werk in stoones/|wenyng þus to plese her maistir&meper; in seing of so faire a temple &Verbar;|But Crist þat had an ynward si&yogh;t&meper; how þe dwellars þerynne|brooken his lawe/ went awey wiþ doulful chere&meper; & tau&yogh;t hise|disciplis of þingis to come/ hou þis temple schulde be destried&meper; | & bad hem bi war þat no man bigile hem/  And soore Crist | wept|vpon þis citee&meper; for mannes bilding stood ful strong/ but bodi &|soule þat he made&meper; to be his owene dwelling place/ were fallen|from keping of his lawe&meper; in to þe sowel of stinking synne/  But|scribis & pharisees weren in cause&meper; of þis greet mischef. as|Mathew seiþ/  wherefore Crist waried hem as hise greetest|enemyes&meper; & alle her folowars to þe worldis ende/ Mat. xxiii o .|'Ve vobis scribe & pharisei qui mundatis quod deforis est&meper; intus|autem estis pleni rapina & immunditia' Vulg. Matt. xxiii. 25 'Vae vobis Scribae et Pharisaei hypocritae, quia|mundatis quod deforis est calicis et paropsidis: intus autem pleni estis rapina|et immunditia.' &Verbar;  Crist seiþ. woo to &yogh;ou
 |scribis & pharises&meper; þat clensen clene. al þat is outward/ but|certis wiþynne &yogh;e ben replete&meper; wiþ miche raveyn & vnclennes W. V. 'Woo to &yogh;ou, scribis and Pharisees, ipocritis, that maken clene|that thing of the cuppe and plater, that is without forth; forsothe with ynne|&yogh;e ben ful of raueyne and unclennesse.'  1388, 'Woo to &yogh;ou, scribis and|Farisees, ypocritis, that clensen the cuppe and the plater with outforth; but|with ynne &yogh;e ben ful of raueyne and unclennesse.' /|&yogh;e bilden þe toumbes of holi prophetis. & wondirfulli honouren her|graues/ but &yogh;e swen &yogh;oure fadris steppis&meper; in purswyng of ri&yogh;twise|blood/ & þise sectis don þe same&meper; but wiþ more malice. in worde|& dede/ O. &yogh;e eddris venymus welpis&meper; hou schullen &yogh;e flee þe|iugement of helle/ þus seiþ oure Lord Iesu Crist/ Wherto make|&yogh;e schry-|-nes to seyntis&meper; & &yogh;it &yogh;e drawen. hangen & brennen |hem þat holden þe weie of Crist&meper; and wandren aftir hise holi|seyntis/ & þou&yogh; þis schewe not in &yogh;oure outwarde dede&meper; &yogh;e don þis|slaw&yogh;tir in worde & wille/ As pharises wiþ bischopis in þe þridde|oure&meper; foriuggid oure Lord wiþ her toungis/ & aftirward kni&yogh;tis|at þe sixte our&meper; hangid his bodi vpon þe cros &Verbar; So þise sectis goon|biforn&meper; to smyte þe peple wiþ her tung/ & aftir kny&yogh;tis of Herowdis|hous&meper; ben ful redi to make an ende &Verbar;  But þe cause of þis pursute&meper;|ben two viciouse extremytees/  Oone is temperal possessioun&meper; þat|wrongfulli standiþ in prestis handis/  þe secounde is synful begry|of mi&yogh;ti men&meper; wiþ hoge bildyng of many waast placis/ and nedis|þei must be mendid&meper; for charite of God to saue her soulis &Verbar;  For|þoo þat maynten þise twoo outstraies&meper; ben ful of many foule disclandris/|bi teching of þe deuel of helle&meper; leest hise retenwe forsake|him/  For þanne | we schal fynde pees in erþe&meper; whanne we kepen |Cristis ordinaunce/ & stynt þou not þou&yogh; þou be sclaundrid&meper; so|if þou lyue iust lijf&meper; to mende þis mys put to þin hond. & þenk|on Cristis rewarde.  Mar. viii o . 'Qui perdiderit animam suam|propter me & euangelium&meper; saluam eam faciet' Vulg. Marc. viii. 35. /  þat is to seie.|who þat haþ loost his lijf&meper; for me & for þe gospel/ he schal make|his soule saaf&meper; in to þe blisse of heuene W. V. 'He that schal leese his soule (that is, his lyf) for me, and the|gospel, schal make it saf.' &Verbar;

9.4:
But fastars in þe fendis chirche&meper; fasten for vngroundid cause/
 |summe fasten for ypocrisie&meper; & schewen hem ruful to þe peple/|suche Crist blameþ in his gospel&meper; & clepiþ hem sorowful ypocritis.|Mat. vi o . 'Cum ieiunatis nolite fieri sicut ypocrite tristes' Vulg. Matt. vi. 16. / for|of þe veyn preising of mannes mouþe&meper; þei han resceyued al her|mede/ Summe wiþdrawen from her wombe&meper; boþe mete & drink to|spare her purse/ and Gregor seiþ þat þis fasting&meper; is for her sachel|& not for God/ and þis is a carful fasting&meper; to peyne oure fleische|& leese oure mede/ as þe wise man seiþ.  Ecc1. vi o .  'Est & aliud|malum quod vidi sub sole & quidem frequens apud homines vir cui|deus dedit diuicias substantiam et honorem. & nihil deest anime sue|ex omnibus que desiderat . nec tribuet ei potestatem deus ut|comedat ex eo. sed homo extraneus vorabit illud/ sed hoc vanitas|& magna miseria'&Verbar; Vulg. Eccles. vi. 1, 2 'Est et aliud malum quod vidi sub sole . . . vir|cui dedit deus divitias et substantiam et honorem &meper; sed homo extraneus|vorabit illud.  Hoc vanitas et magna miseria est.' Þer is also þe wise man seiþ&meper; þat he sau&yogh;|vndir þe sunne/ anoþir yuel þat | is ful rijf&meper; & comune amonge þe |peple/ a man þat God haþ &yogh;yuen richesse&meper; wiþ catel & miche|worschip/ & no þing failiþ to his lijf&meper; of al þat he desiriþ/ but him|wantiþ grace & powere&meper; to eete or take his parte þerof/ But a man|þat is a straungere&meper; schal deuoure it aftir his dai/ but þis a sorowful|vanite&meper; & a greete wrecchidnes W. V. 'There is and an other euel, that I sa&yogh; under the sunne: and|forsothe ofte anentis men.  A man to whom God &yogh;af richessis, and substaunce,|and worshepe; and no thing lacketh to his soule of alle thingis that he|desireth; and God &yogh;yueth not power to hym, that he ete of it, but a straunge|man shal deuouren it.  This is vanyte, and gret wrecchidnesse.'  1388, 'Also|another yuel is, which Y si&yogh; undur the sunne; and certis it is oft usid anentis|men.  A man is, to whom God &yogh;af richessis and catel, and onour; and no|thing faileth to his soule of alle thingis which he desirith; and God &yogh;yueth|not power to him, that he ete therof, but a straunge man shal deuoure it.|This is vanyte, and a greet wretchidnesse.' &Verbar; Summe fasten for a medicyn&meper;|for to gete hem bodili heele/ neiþir for God ne for þe soule&meper; but|for to clense her beaute/ seint Ierom blameþ þis fasting&meper; & þat on|a ful blessid maner &Verbar;  'Tunc preclara est apud deum abstinentia|corporis&meper; cum animus intus ieiunat a viciis/ Quid prodest corpus|tenuare inedia&meper; cum animus intus tumescit superbia/  Hec|Ieromus super Amos &Verbar;  Þat is to seie.  þanne abstinence of|bodi is clere to God&meper; whanne þe mynde fastiþ from vicis/ what|profiteþ it to tere þe bodi wiþ hounger&meper; whanne mynde wiþynne|swelliþ wiþ pride &Verbar; what fasting is þis to wiþdrawe lijflod
 |from þe beli&meper; & to be wood in envie or foule hastite? God seiþ bi | þe prophete Isaie. lviii o . 'Ecce ad lites | & contenciones ieiunatis|etcetera' Vulg. Isaias lviii. 4. idem Zaca. viii o . Vulg. Zech. vii. 5, 6. 'Loo whanne &yogh;e fasten &yogh;e maken strijf&meper;|& debatis among &yogh;oure silf' W. V. 'Lo! to ples and to striues &yogh;ee fasten.'  1388, 'Lo! &yogh;e fasten to|chidyngis and stryuyngis.' / þis is not þe fasting þat I cheese&meper;|seiþ þe Lord God/ And siþen þe fende neiþir eetiþ ne drinkiþ&meper;|neiþir is wlappid in precious cloþis/ &yogh;it he schal be euir in peyne&meper;|for him lackiþ charite &Verbar;  þanne is þis an evidence&meper; þat alle suche|recheles fastars/ ben membris in þe fendis chirche&meper; in folowyng|her fadir &Verbar;

9.6:
But preiars in þe fendis chirche&meper; maken miche noise/ mumling|wiþ her lippis&meper; þei reche neuir what/ so þat men preise fast.  her|feyned occupacioun/ as Crist seiþ in his gospel.  Mat. xv o &Verbar;|'Populus hic labijs me honorat&meper; cor autem eorum longe est a me' Vulg. Matt. xv. 8. &Verbar;|Þis peple worschipiþ me wiþ her lippis&meper; but her herte is feer fro | me W. V. 'This peple honoureth me with lippis, forsothe her herte is fer fro|me.' / Lord! whanne þi body is in þe chirche | and þi herte in þe
 |world/ or cumbrid wiþ vnclene þou&yogh;tis&meper; & wiþ veyn fantasies/ & þi|tounge in minstralsie&meper; or on lewid iangling/ & þi wittis oueresett&meper;|wiþ seculere nedis/ art þou not þanne wrechidli diuidid in þi silf MS. in þi þi silf. ?|Seint Iame seiþ. i o . 'Non estimet homo ille quod accipiat aliquid|a domino' Vulg. Jac i. 7. / suppose not þis veyn man&meper; þat he mai take ony þing|of þe Lord W. V. 'Therfore gesse not the ilke man, that he shal take ony thing of|the Lord.' / he mai in nowise be herde in preiour&meper; þat suffreþ his|herte to sleepe in synne &Verbar; And efte God seiþ bi Isaie&meper; in general|wordis to wickid lyuars. i o . 'Cum multiplicaueritis orationes uestras.|ego non exaudiam. quia manus uestre plene sanguinum sunt' Vulg. Isaias i. 15 'Cum multiplicaveritis orationem, non exaudiam: manus|enim vestrae sanguine plenae sunt.' &Verbar;|whanne &yogh;e han multiplied &yogh;oure preiours&meper; I schal not heere &yogh;ou|graciouseli/ & þe cause whi is þis&meper; for &yogh;oure handis ben ful of|blood W. V. 'Whan zee shul multeplien orisoun, I shal not heren; forsothe|&yogh;oure hondis ben ful of blod.'  1388, 'Whanne &yogh;e multiplien preyer, Y schal|not here; for whi &yogh;oure hondis ben ful of blood.' / þat is. &yogh;oure werkis ben ful of synne&meper; þat parten &yogh;ou & me|atwynne/ Þus seiþ þe Lord God &Verbar;  But wite &yogh;e wel &yogh;e viciouse|preestis&meper; þat gon from Crist in viciouse lyuyng/ and wil not swe|hise holi steppis&meper; but | terren him from dai to dai/ þerfore &yogh;oure |preiours ben dispisid&meper; as Crist seiþ þat mai not lie.  Mat. xxiii o .|'ve vobis scribe & pharisei ypocrite qui comeditis domos viduarum|orationes longas orantes. propter hoc accipietis iudicium amplius' Vulg. Matt. xxiii. 14. &Verbar;|Woo to &yogh;ou scribis & pharisees ypocritis/ þat eeten þe housis of|widowis&meper; bi &yogh;oure long preiers/ for þis þing &yogh;e schal take&meper; þe|largear iugement W. V. 'Woo to &yogh;ou, scribis and Pharisees, ypocritis, that eten the housis|of widues, in longe preier preyinge: for this thing &yogh;e schulen take the more|dom.'  1388, 'Wo to &yogh;ou, scribis and Farisees, ipocritis, that eten the housis|of widowis, and preien bi longe prier; for this thing &yogh;e schulen take more|doom.' &Verbar;  vpon þis seiþ Crisostom. om. xliiii. 'Inposturas|ypocritarum mulieres non possunt facile cognoscere &c' S. Ioan. Chrysostomus, Homilia XLIV (Opera , ed. 1547, tom. ii, col.|1052). /|Þe slei&yogh;tis or þe whilis of ypocritis&meper; wommen mai not li&yogh;tli knowe/|& bicause of her religioun&meper; þei wile soone bowe to hem/ for þat
 |þei be neische&meper; & wanen aboute as þe wynde &Verbar; Þis doctour markiþ|twoo special causis&meper; whi þei drawen to widowis housis/ Oone is|for wommen þat ben weddid&meper; & vndir þe power of mannes daunger/|dore not &yogh;yue þise worldli goodis&meper; wiþouten counseile of her|housbond &Verbar;  Anoþir.  widowes ben ful of pite. to &yogh;yue whanne þei | ben pitousli axid/ | and han no man to werne þis dede&meper; for her good|is at her wille/ & for þis ende þise flatiryng gloosars&meper; moost raþest|haunten widowis housis/ Crist whischeþ hem woo & warneþ oure|prestis&meper; þat þei forsake þis synful manere/ for it is to cursid|a dede&meper; to hide synne vndir peyntid religioun/ & cloþe wickidnes|in ypocrisie&meper; til it þe trowid for verry pite/ & in þe armour of|Iesu Crist&meper; þei don þe fendis werkis of helle/ whanne þei largen|her long preiars&meper; as nettis þat ben spradde abrood/ & wiþ þis craft|þei cacchen awey&meper; þe goodis of þise celi widowis/ Þise widowis we|schullen vndirstonde&meper; boþe for men & for wymmen/ þat wanten|wisdam of Iesu Crist&meper; þe whiche is spouse of mannes soule/ for|Iesu Crist no where delitiþ&meper; but in hem þat louen his lawe &Verbar;

9.19:
But mynystrars of sacramentis&meper; þat ben in þe fendis chirche/|mynystren þise sacramentis&meper; & treeten hem vnworþili/ & alle|suche boþe lerned & lewid&meper; ben Iudas goostly children/ for he took|þe sacrament&meper; at Cristis hooli sooper/ where Crist dalt his bodi in|breed&meper; as oþir apostlis diden/ & drank wiþ hem his blood in wyn&meper;|but wiþ a viciouse conscience/ wherfore þe deuel entrid in him&meper; &|he bitraied his Lord/ Þus it is wiþ þe fendis children&meper; whanne þei|resceyue þe sacramentis/ þei gon to hem vnworþili&meper; & so to her|dampnacioun &Verbar;  Summe wiþ polutid handis&meper; & wiþ a stinking|careyn/ as Parisieus seiþ&meper; & rehersiþ Austin/ 'Nocte amator|veneris&meper; cras consecrator filii virginis/ Deus auertit MS. avertiþ. aurem suam&meper;|ab oratione talium' &Verbar; Þat is to seie.  He þat is on þe ny&yogh;t&meper; þe|louer of leccherie/ & in þe morne a sacrar&meper; of þe maidens sone/|God turneþ awey hise eeris&meper; from suche mennes preiours &Verbar; Manye|feiþful doctours&meper; forbeden ful strei&yogh;tli/ for to take ony sacramentis&meper; | of suche preestis handis/ | But now it is & euer schal be&meper; vnto þe|worldis ende/ foolis fynden conventiclis&meper; þat haasten hem to helle/|Summe þer ben as Symoundis eiris&meper; þat sellen þise sacramentis/|& summe ben redi wiþ her money&meper; as chapmen in a feire/ to bie|of þise marchauntis marchaundise&meper; merite as þei wenen/ but boþe|þe biggers & þe sellers&meper; disceruen endeles peyne/ Summe seien|'haue here my moneye&meper; for cristenyng of my childe'/ summe seyn|'haue here þis money&meper; & soyle me of my synnes'/ summe seyn|'haue here þis money&meper; & sing for me a messe' &Verbar; Summe seyn 'haue|þis money&meper; & graunt me þi pardon'/ summe seyn 'haue þis money&meper;|for þou hast made þis mariage'/ summe seyn 'haue þis money &
 |sacre me to presthod'/ summe seyn 'haue þis money&meper; for þou hast|often visitid me'/ summe seyn 'haue here þis money&meper; & good sire|preie for me' &Verbar; Summe maken lettris&meper; for sotiler ypocrisie/ to selle|alle her suffragis&meper; where euere þei fynden þe chapman/ þat wole|paie lar-|-geli þerfore&meper; þanne is þe bargayn made/ Lord hou reden |þise fendis lymes&meper; þe decre saluator Gratian, Decreti Pars Secunda, causa i, quaest. iii, c. viii (Migne,|tom. 187, col. 549, 550). / or studien Goddis lawe&meper;|in Dedis of þe Apostlis/ where suche marchaundise is dampned&meper;|for þus it is seide of cursid Symound/ Actus viii o ./ 'Cum vidisset|autem symon quia per imposicionem manus daretur spiritus sanctus&meper;|optulit eis peccuniam dicens &Verbar; Date & mihi hanc potestatem vt|cuicumque MS. circumque. imposuero manus accipiat spiritum sanctum/ Petrus|autem dixit ad eum. Pecunia tua tecum sit in perdicionem&meper; quoniam|donum dei existimasti peccunia possideri/ Non est tibi pars neque|sors. in sermone isto' Vulg. Act. viii. 18-21. / Þat is to seie.  Forsoþe whanne Symon|magus had seyn&meper; þat bi touching of þe apostlis handis/ þe Holi|Goost was &yogh;ouun to þe peple&meper; he profrid hem money & seide to|hem/ &yogh;yue &yogh;e to me also þis powere&meper; þat whom so euere I touche|wiþ handis/ may resceyue þe hooli goost&meper; forsoþe þanne Petir seide|to him/ þi money be wiþ þee for vs&meper; take it þi silf to þi dampnacioun/|for þou trowist | þe &yogh;ift of God&meper; to be hadde in sale for |moneye/ þer is no parte neiþir lott&meper; to þee in þis sermon of God W. V. 'Forsoth whanne Symound hadde seyn, for the Hooli Gost was|&yogh;ouun by puttyng on of the hond of apostlis, he offride to hem money, seyinge,|&yogh;yue &yogh;e to me and this power, that to whom euere I schal putte on hondis, he|receyue the Hooly Gost.  Forsoth Petre seide to him, Thi money be with|thee into perdicioun, for thou gessidist the &yogh;ifte of God for to be had, (or|weeldid), by money.  Part is not to thee, nethir sort, in this word.'  1388,|'And whanne Symount hadde seyn, that the Hooly Goost was &yogh;ouun bi|leiyng on of the hoondis of the apostlis, and he proferide to hem money, and|seide, &yogh;yue &yogh;e also to me this power, that whom euere Y schal leye on my|hoondis, that he resseyue the Hooli Goost.  But Petir seide to hym, Thi|money be with thee into perdicioun, for thou gessidist the &yogh;ifte of God schulde|be had for monei.  There is no part, ne sort to thee, in this word.' &Verbar;|Þanne þise þat we han markid aforn&meper; in þis ben verrey Symoundis|eiris/ for þei wenen whanne þei han money&meper; to graunt þe peple|þise goostli &yogh;iftis/ and Symon is dampned & alle hise folowars&meper; hou|miche more raþer þise cursid takars/ For if seint Petir hadde
 |taken þis money&meper; he hadde &yogh;ouun leue to vse symonye/ but Petir|forsook it & blamed þis man&meper; & &yogh;aue a rule þat euer schal last/ þat|cursiþ & dampneþ boþe þe &yogh;yuars & takars&meper; for boþe partijs ben|symonyentis/ O. Iudas made a couenaunt&meper; wiþ þe Iewis for þritti|platis/ and soold his maistir Iesu Crist&meper; bitraiyng his bodi in to|her hondis/ whanne he cam cheueli for to die&meper; & his deeþ is oure|redempcioun/ þerfore his name is cursid Iudas&meper; & worþili for his | fals trayne/ But hise children don myche warre&meper; | in selling þe|sacramentis & for lesse prijs/ þat ben vndeedli & moun not suffre&meper;|neiþir ony profite comeþ of suche sale/ But veniaunce here & ellis|where&meper; alas whanne wole þise wrecchis be war &Verbar;

9.31:
But prestis & kny&yogh;tis&meper; of þis synne ben moost to blame/ Prestis|þat schulden be goostli lechis&meper; and recounseile þe peple/ bi good|counseile to her God&meper; & heele hem wiþ his lawe/ what wiþ pride &|coueitise&meper; & many fleischeli lustis/ þise prestis ben so blyndid&meper;|þat þei knowe no wisdam/ for Iob seiþ.  xxviii o . 'vbi invenitur|sapientia&meper; non enim in terra suauiter viuencium' Vulg. Job xxviii. 12, 13 'Sapientia vero ubi invenitur? ... nec invenitus|in terra suaviter viventium.' / Iob axiþ þis|questioun&meper; where wisdam mai be founden/ anoon he answeriþ wiþ|þe spirit of God&meper; not in þe lond of lusti lyuars W. V. 'Wisdam forsothe, wher is it founde? ... ne it is founde in the|lond of sweteli lyuende men.' / And vpon þis|seiþ Gregor in hise morals&meper; þise wordis of greet sorow. to hem þat|ben gilti/ 'Quisquis presentis vite voluptatibus pascitur procul|dubio eterne sapientie intellectu separatur' Gregorius Magnus, Moralium Lib. XVIII, cap. xli. 66 (Migne, tom. 76,|col. 75). &Verbar;  Þat is to seie. who|þat is fedde&meper; wiþ lustis of þis present lijf/ wiþouten ony doute&meper;|þat man is departid/ fro þe vndirstanding&meper; of euerlasting wisdam &Verbar;|And siþen þise prestis&meper; ben moost &yogh;ouun/ to þise fleischeli lustis&meper;|þei failen | goostli si&yogh;t/ and wisdam to ransake&meper; ony goostli |sijknes/ or to serche al aboute&meper; þe perel of a wounde/ & &yogh;it þei ben|presumptuouse&meper; to profre fals medicyn/ & vndirtake greet curis&meper;
 |for to make hem hool/ But þei hirten myche sorer&meper; þan þei were|aforn/ as þe Lord moneþ him&meper; bi þe prophet Ieremye. Iere. viii o .|'Sanabant contricionem populi mei ad ignominiam dicentes.  Pax.|pax. cum non esset pax/ Confusi sunt qui abhominacionem fecerunt/|Quinimo confusione MS. confuc&omacr;e. non sunt confusi&meper; & erubescere nescierunt' Vulg. Jer. viii. 11, 12 'Sanabant contritionem filiae populi,' etc. &Verbar;|Þise prestis MS. perstis. heliden þe contricioun of my peple&meper; wiþ schenschip|or wiþ schame/ þat is wiþ foule symonye&meper; as we rehersid aforn/|and þei seyn pees pes&meper; whanne þer was no pees/ þei ben worþi to|be schent&meper; þat han done abhominacioun/ miche raþer in þis confucioun&meper;|þei be not confoundid/ for þei can not be aschamed&meper; of|her owene vilenye W. V. '(Thei) heleden the tobrosing of the do&yogh;ter of my puple to|shenshipe, seiende, Pes, pes, whan ther was not pes.  Confoundid thei ben,|for abhomynacioun thei diden; but myche more by confusioun thei ben not|confoundid, and shamen thei kouthen not.'  1388, 'Thei heeliden the sorowe|of the dou&yogh;tir of my puple to schenschipe, seiynge, Pees, pees, whanne no pees|was.  Thei ben schent, for thei diden abhomynacioun; &yogh;he, rather thei weren|not schent bi schenschipe, and kouden not be aschamed.' / Þus seiþ þe Lord God/ and efte he seiþ ca o ..|xxiii o .  'A prophetis enim Ierusalem egressa est pollucio super | | omnem terram. hec dicit dominus. Nolite audire verba prophetarum|qui prophetant vobis & decipiunt vos/ visionem cordis sui locuntur&meper;|non de ore domini/ Dicunt hijs qui blasfemant me. locutus est|dominus pax erit vobis & omni qui ambulant in prauitatem cordis|sui dixerunt. non veniat super uos malum' Vulg. Jer. xxiii. 15, 16 'A prophetis enim ... haec dicit dominus|exercituum,' etc. &Verbar; From þe prechours|of þe chirche&meper; comeþ defoiling vppon al þe erþe/ þise þingis seiþ|þe Lord/ Nile &yogh;e heere þe wordis of þise precheours&meper; þat prechen|& disceyuen &yogh;ou | þei speken þe visioun of her herte&meper; but not of þe|Lordis mouþe/ Þei seyn to þoo þat blasfemen me&meper; þe Lord spekiþ|þat pees schal be to &yogh;ou/ & þei han seide to iche a man&meper; þat|walkiþ in schrewidnes of his herte.  þer schal non yuel cum vpon|&yogh;ou W. V. 'Fro the profetus forsothe of Jerusalem is gon out defouling upon|al erthe.  These thingus seith the Lord of ostus, Wileth not heren the wrdus|of the profetes, that profecien to &yogh;ou, and desceyven &yogh;ou; the viseoun of ther|herte thei speken, not of the mouth of the Lord.  They seyn to them that|blasfemen me, The Lord spac, Pes shal be to &yogh;ou; and to eche that goth in|the shreudnesse of his herte thei seiden, Ther shal not come up on &yogh;ou euel.' &Verbar;  And Gregor seiþ.  'Causa ruine populi&meper; sunt sacerdotes
 |mali' Gregorius Magnus, Homiliae in Evangelia , Lib. II, Hom. xxxix. 2 (Migne,|tom. 75, col. 1295). / yuel prestis ben cause of ruyn or mischef of þe peple/ and|no wondir. for whanne þat li&yogh;t is quenchid . þat schulde schyne|in | prestis/ þanne is þer miche stink&meper; wiþ wickid sauour/ & |blyndnes þat combriþ&meper; þe leder & þe folowar/ in to þe derckness|of helle&meper; þe gospel beriþ witnes/ Mat. xv o . Luk. vi o . 'Cecus|autem si ceco ducatum prestet&meper; nonne ambo in fouiam cadunt' Vulg. Matt. xv. 14 'Caecus autem si caeco ducatum praestet, ambo in|foveam cadunt.'  Luke vi. 39 'Numquid potest caecus caecum ducere, nonne|ambo in foveam cadunt?' &Verbar;|Whanne þe blynde lediþ þe blynde. falle þei not þanne boþe in to|þe lake? W. V. '&YOGH;if a blynd man &yogh;eue ledynge to a blynd man, bothe fallen doun|in to the diche.' &yogh;his pleynli &Verbar; Þe former blynde is þe preest/ þat wantiþ|vndirstonding/ for þou&yogh; he haue lettrure&meper; & faile in good lyuyng/|þanne he is a blynde prest&meper; of whom Crist spekiþ/ as þe comune|gloose seiþ.  'Frustra iactat legis noticiam&meper; qui operibus destruit|doctrinam'/ Aboute nou&yogh;t he boostiþ&meper; þe knowing of Goddis lawe/|þat distrieþ þe loore&meper; wiþ his wickid werkis/ Þe toþir blynde is|man & womman&meper; þat tristen in suche prestis&meper; to lede hem in þe|weie of lijf&meper; & bringe hem to saluacioun &Verbar; But Crist haþ iuggid|þise boþe parties&meper; to falle in to þe doungun/ Of suche prestis|comeþ debate&meper; in al þis brood world/ þat distur-|-bliþ verry pees&meper; |& crieþ open veniaunce/ And þise prechours ben no prechours&meper;|but oonli in name/ as a luschborue is clepid a peny&meper; þat is ri&yogh;t|nou&yogh;t worþe &Verbar;

10.3:
Alle þe membris of a man&meper; traueilen in her ordir/ iche for to|socour oþir&meper; & noon for to hindir/ but for to do her comune
 |helpe&meper; to profite of þe bodi &Verbar; Þus it is of þe membris&meper; þat ben in|Cristis chirche/ for it is a goostli bodi&meper; þat growiþ wiþ hir|membris/ þere oone failiþ anoþir helpiþ&meper; til þis corde be made &Verbar;|Summe haue myche of wisdam&meper; to knowe holi writ/ summe haue|faire eloquence&meper; to preche it to þe peple/ summe han myche of &Verbar;goostli strengþe&meper; to suffre tribulacioun/ summe han pite & releuen&meper; |her pore nedi nei&yogh;boris/ summe tenten vertuouseli to mynystir þe|sacramentis/ summe sti&yogh;en hi&yogh;eli&meper; to rest in heuenli likyngis/ But|alle suche þingis ben in comune&meper; to hem þat schal be saued/ as þe|prophet seiþ. Ps. cxv./ 'Particeps ego sum omnium timencium te&meper;|& custodiencium mandata tua' Vulg. Ps. cxviii. 63. / Þe prophete spekiþ in þe|persoone&meper; of þe general chirche/ Lord I am partenere&meper; of alle|þat dreden þee/ & of alle þat kepen&meper; þi hooli comaundementis W. V. 'Parcener I am of all men dredende thee: and of kepende thin|hestis.'  1388, 'I am parcener of alle that dreden thee; and kepen thin|heestis.' /|Þis techeþ also þe comune crede&meper; of þe .xii. apostlis/ In an article|of oure feiþ&meper; þat must nede be grauntid/ 'Sanctorum communionem.'|comunyng of seintis/ For what þat euer be done in|Rome&meper; or in ony oþir placis&meper; if þat þing be couenable&meper; in þe si&yogh;t|of God/ þanne is it comune to alle þise membris&meper; þat seruen God|in vertu/ to helpe hem to her endeles ioye&meper; as we han seide aforn/|Herto acordiþ seint Ierom&meper; vpon þis tixte of Cristis gospel/|Mat. xvi o . 'Tibi dabo claues regni celorum' Vulg. Matt. xvi. 19. / Crist seid to Petir&meper;|& in him to alle his folowars/ to þee and alle | suche as þou art&meper; |I schal &yogh;yue þe keyes of þe rewme of heuenes W. V. 'To thee I shal &yogh;eue the keies of the kyngdam of heuenes.' &Verbar;  Þise twoo keies.|þe tone is kunnyng of worde&meper; þe toþir is power of presthood/ Þe|rewme of heuenes&meper; is þe chirche here in erþe/ Ierom seiþ&meper; & þe|maistir of sentence rehersiþ him/ li o . IIii o . dist. xix.  'Habent|inquit eandem iudiciariam potestatem omnes ecclesie ministri in|episcopis & presbiteris sicut petrus. sed ideo petrus eam specialiter|accepit vt omnes intelligant quod quicumque ab vnitate fidei &|societate ecclesie se separauerit. nec a peccatis solui. nec celum|potest ingredi' Petrus Lombardus, Sententiarum Libri quatuor , IV, dist. xix (Migne,|tom. 191, col. 890). &Verbar;  Alle þe mynystris of þe chirch&meper; in bischopis
 |& in prestis/ han þe same iudiciarij powere&meper; as seint Petir|hadde/ But þerfore Petir speciali&meper; tooke of God þis power/|þat alle men moun vndirstand&meper; þat who euer depart him/ fro|vnite of stedfast feiþ&meper; & felaschip of þis chirche/ he mai neiþir|be asoyled&meper; from bondis of hise synnes/ neiþir he mai entre&meper; in to|þe blisse of heuene &Verbar;

11.1:
But for þat we reproue þise synnes&meper; þis yuel parti grucchiþ/ and|pursueþ wiþ strong hand&meper; to prisoun & to slee/ þerfore must we|lerne þe loore&meper; of Cristis hooli gospel/  Mat. v o . 'Beati estis cum|maledixerint vobis homines & persecuti vos fuerint & dixerint|omne malum aduersum vos mencientes propter me &c' Vulg. Matt. v. 11 'Beati estis cum maledixerint vobis et persecuti,' etc. / &yogh;e ben|blessid whanne men han oursid &yogh;ou. & han pursued &yogh;ou. & seid al | yuel | a&yogh;ens &yogh;ou lying for me&meper; Ioye & be myry. for &yogh;oure mede is|miche in heuenes W. V. '&YOGH;ee shulen be blessid, when men shulen curse &yogh;ou, and shulen|pursue &yogh;ou, and shulen say al yuel a&yogh;eins &yogh;ou lee&yogh;ing for me.  Joye &yogh;ee with|yn forth, and glade &yogh;ee with out forth, for &yogh;oure meede is plenteuouse in|heuenes.' / And also seint Petir seiþ. I. Pe. iii o . 'Siquid|patimini propter iusticiam&meper; beati' Vulg. 1 Pet. iii. 14. &Verbar;  Whanne þat &yogh;e suffren ony|þing for ri&yogh;twisenesse&meper; blessid mut &yogh;e be W. V. 'But if &yogh;e suffren ony thing for ri&yogh;twisenesse, &yogh;e ben blessid.' &Verbar;  Seint Poul affermeþ|þis sentence&meper; þat Goddis trewe seruauntis/ schullen haue peyne in|þis lijf&meper; to kepe hem in vertu/  II. Thimo. iii o . 'Omnes qui pie|volunt viuere in christo iesu&meper; persecucionem pacientur' Vulg. 2 Tim. iii. 12. &Verbar;  Alle
 |þat euer wole lyue mekeli in Crist Iesu&meper; schal suffre persecucioun W. V. 'Alle men that wolen lyue piteuously in Crist Jhesu, schulen|suffre persecucioun.'  1388, 'Alle men that wolen lyue feithfull in Crist|Jhesu schulen suffre persecucioun.' &Verbar;|And seint Luk seiþ of þe wordis of Poul&meper; in dedis of þe apostlis.|Actus xiiii o . 'Per multas tribulaciones oportet nos intrare in regnum|dei' Vulg. Acts xiv. 21. &Verbar;  Bi manye tribulaciouns. it bihoueþ vs to entre&meper; in to þe|rewme of God W. V. 'By manye tribulaciouns it behoueth us for to entre into the|kingdom of heuenes.' / And þus seiþ þe prophete. Ps. xxxiii. 'Multe tribulaciones|iustorum&meper; et de omnibus hijs liberabit MS. biberauit. eos dominus' Vulg. Ps. xxxiii. 19. /|many be þe tribulaciouns&meper; þat fallen to þe ri&yogh;twise/ and from hem|alle whanne tyme comeþ&meper; God schal delyuer hem W. V. 'Manye tribulaciouns of the ri&yogh;twise; and of alle these schal|delyuere them the Lord.'  1388, 'Many tribulaciouns ben of iust men; and|the Lord schal delyuere hem fro alle these.' &Verbar; Crist bihi&yogh;t þis|maner of lijf&meper; to hise owene disciplis/ and | &yogh;aue hem in counfort þat |þei schal haue&meper; a graciouse delyueraunce/ for þanne schal blisse be|miche þe swetter&meper; whanne þei comen þerto/ Ion. xvi o ./ 'Amen amen|dico vobis. quia plorabitis & flebitis vos mundus autem gaudebit|vos autem contristabimini. sed tristicia uestra vertetur in gaudium|& gaudium vestrum. nemo tollet a vobis' Vulg. John xvi. 20, 22. &Verbar;  Treweli I seie to &yogh;ou|þe trouþe&meper; &yogh;e schal greete & weepe/ forsoþe þis world schal ioye&meper;|& &yogh;e schal be ful heuy/ and aftir þis &yogh;oure heuynes&meper; schal be|turned in to ioie/ & &yogh;oure ioye schal be so siker&meper; þat no man|schal take it fro &yogh;ou W. V. 'Treuli treuli, I seye to &yogh;ou, for &yogh;e schulen morne and wepe.|forsothe the world schal enioye; forsoþe &yogh;e schulen be sorwful, but &yogh;oure|sorwe schal turne into ioye, and no man schal take fro &yogh;ou &yogh;oure ioye.' / And for þis ioie schulde sauour wel&meper; to|hem þat ben hise louears/ he sendeþ hem tribulacioun&meper; as seint|Gregor seiþ/ 'Deus electis suis iter ostendit asperum&meper; ne si|delectentur in via obliuiscantur eorum que sunt in patria' Gregorius Magnus, Moralium Lib. XXIII, cap. xxiv. 47 (Migne, tom.|76, cols. 279, 280). / &|iterum/ 'tribulaciones que in hoc mundo nos premunt. nos ad|deum ire compellunt'/  Iterum. 'Oculos quos culpa claudit&meper;
 |pena aperit' Gregorius Magnus, Moralium Lib. XV, cap. li. 58 (Migne, tom. 75,|col. 1111). &Verbar; God schewiþ to hise chosen&meper; scharpnes in þis | iourney/ lest bihap | if þei delited hem&meper; in þis deedli weye/ þei|my&yogh;t for&yogh;ete þe þingis&meper; þat ben in heuenli countre/ Tribulaciouns|þat brisen vs doun&meper; in þis wrecchid world/ þei constreynen vs to|go to God&meper; þat li&yogh;tli my&yogh;t be dampned/ for þoo i&yogh;en þat synne|closiþ&meper; peyne makiþ hem open/ and many a man þat hauntiþ|þeeft&meper; wiþ manye oþir synnes/ if þei were lame. blynde. or crokid&meper;|of Goddis visitacioun/ þei schulden cese & serue her God&meper; & do|penaunce ful treweli/ as Crisostom seiþ.  om. iii. 'Anima spiritus|est & spirituales penas timet.  carnales non timet. verum & sancti|penas huius seculi contempnunt & futurum iudicium timent vbi|spiritus cruciantur &Verbar;  Caro autem spirituales penas non timet.|carnales autem timet. ideo mali non cessant peccare nisi eos iudicia|carnalia & terrena conpescant propterea mittet dominus super|seruos suos carnales temptaciones ut conbusta caro non concupiscat|malum' S. Ioan. Chrysostomus, ( Homilia III, Opera , ed. 1547, tom. ii, col. 763). &Verbar; Þe soule is a spirit&meper; & drediþ spiritual peynes/ but it | wole not drede&meper; | þe peynes of þe fleische/ & þerfore seyntis|dispisiden&meper; peynes of þis world/ & dreden þe last iugement&meper; where|spiritis ben turmentid/ Forsoþe þe fleische cannot drede&meper; goostli|peynes to cum/ but he drediþ in þis lijf&meper; to suffre ony peynes/|þerfore þe yuel cessen not&meper; for to do synne/ but if iugement of þe|fleische&meper; constreynen hem to be stille/ & for þis cause þe Lord schal|sende&meper; vpon hise seruauntis/ sore punysching to her fleische&meper; &|oþir tribulaciouns/ þat lust of þe fleische mai be sweilid&meper; from|coueiting of yuel.  We must nede breke þe nutt&meper; if we wole haue|þe kirnel/ we must nedis suffre traueile&meper; if we desiren rest/ So|must we nede suffre peyne&meper; if we wole cum to blisse &Verbar;

12.4:
Þe .III. heest/ Þe þridde comaundement of God is þis. Exodi. xx o . 'Memento|vt diem sabbati sanctifices. vi. diebus operaberis & facies opera|tua. septimo autem die sabbati domini dei tui est.  Non facies | omne opus tu & filius tuus & filia tua & seruus tuus et | ancilla|tua iumentum tuum & aduena qui est intra portas tuas. vi. diebus|fecit deus celum & terram & mare & omnia que in eis sunt. &|requieuit in die septimo/ Iccirco benedixit deus diei sabbati &|sanctificauit illud' Vulg. Ex. xx. 8-11 'Memento ... facies omnia opera tua ... Non|facies omne opus in eo, tu et filius tuus ... Sex enim diebus,' etc. / Þat is to seie.  Haue mynde þat þou halowe|þin halidai.  In .vi. daies þou schalt worche&meper; & do alle þin owne|werkis/ forsoþe þe seuenþe dai. is þe sabot of þi Lord. þou schalt|not do ony seruyle werk/ þise .vi. schal kepe þis holidai/ þi sone|& þi dou&yogh;ter/ þi seruaunt & þin handmayde/ þi beest & þi|straunger þat is wiþynne þi &yogh;atis &Verbar;  In .vi. daies God mad heuene|& erþe & þe see. & alle þingis þat ben in hem&meper; & he restid in þe|seuenþe dai/ þerfore God blessid þe dai of þe saboth&meper; & made it holi W. V. 'Haue mynde to halwe thin holy day; sixe daies thow shalt|worche and doon alle thi werkis; the seuenthe forsothe dai is the haliday of|the Lord thi God; thow shalt not doon al werk, thow, and thi sone, and thi|dow&yogh;ter, and thi seruaunt, and thin handmayden thi beeste, and comlyng|that is with ynne thi &yogh;atis; sixe forsothe daies God made heuene and erthe,|the see, and alle thingis that ben in hem, and he restide the seuenthe day;|therfore the Lord blisside to the holiday and halwide it.'  1388, 'Haue thou|mynde, that thou halowe the dai of the sabat; in sixe daies thou schalt|worche and schalt do alle thi werkis; forsothe in the seuenthe day is the|sabat of thi Lord God; thou schalt not do ony werk, thou, and thi sone, and|thi dou&yogh;tir, and thi seruaunt, and thin handmaide, thi werk beest, and the|comelyng which is withynne thi &yogh;atis; for in sixe dayes God made heuene|and erthe, the see, and alle thingis that ben in tho, and restide in the seuenthe|dai; herfor the Lord blesside the dai of the sabat, and halewide it.' / A&yogh;en þis comaundement&meper; þe fende in hise membris/ &yogh;yueþ leue|to chapmen&meper; to bie & to selle/ &yogh;he wiþynne þe sauntwary&meper; on þe|holi sundai/ and vitileris of þe countre&meper; holden comune market &Verbar;|&yogh;et se more wlatsumnes&meper; a&yogh;ens þis Goddis heest/ greet feires of|þe &yogh;eere&meper; for þe moost partie&meper; ben sett on | þe saboth dai&meper; bi þe |fendis counceile/ God tooke ful hidouse wreeche&meper; vpon þe children|of Isrel/ whanne þei wrou&yogh;t seruyle werke. vpon her saboth dai/|as it is writen. Exo. xxxi o . 'Custodite sabbatum meum sanctum|enim est vobis. qui polluerit illud. morte morietur/ qui fecerit in|eo opus peribit anima illius de medio populi sui' Vulg. Ex. xxxi. 14. &Verbar; Þat is to seie.|Halowe &yogh;e my saboth&meper; forsoþe it is holi to &yogh;ou/ who þat haþ|defoulid it&meper; he schal be deed/ & he þat doiþ ony seruyle werke|þerynne&meper; his lijf schal perische fro þe myddis of his peple W. V. 'Kepith myn holi day, holi forsothe it is to &yogh;ow, who so poluteth|it, with deth dye he; who so doth in it werk. shal perishe the lijf of hym fro|the myddil of his puple.'  1388, 'Kepe &yogh;e my sabat, for it is hooli to &yogh;ou; he|that defoulith it, schal die bi deeth, the soule of hym, that doith werk in the|sabat, schal perische fro the myddis of his puple.' / & so|for gedring of stikkis&meper; on þe saboth dai/ a man bi Goddis bidding|was stooned to þe deeþ &Verbar; þerfore Neemyas&meper; a man þat dredde|God/ wolde suffre noon to bie ne selle&meper; on þe sabot dai/ wiþynne|þe &yogh;atis of Ierusalem&meper; neiþir aboute þe wallis/ and chargid alle|vitileris&meper; þat þei schulde ceese/ And if þei wolde not take heede&meper;|þei schulde fele his hondis/ for he þou&yogh;t to werre on hem&meper; as on|Goddis enemyes/ but þei wolde obeie to God&meper; in halowing of his|saboth/ Þis processe is | writen in þe book of Neemyas&meper; þe last |chapitir Vulg. Neh. xiii. 15-22. &Verbar;  Loo hou strei&yogh;tli þe Iewis&meper; kepten Goddis bidding/|& hou God smot hem wiþ bodili peyne&meper; whanne þat þei dide|forfet/  But cristen men maken her boost&meper; þat þei ben more|perfi&yogh;t/ in seruyse of her Lord God&meper; þan euer were þe Iewis/|who þat euer mekeli&meper; proueþ his word in dede/ þanne mai he
 |seie boldli&meper; þat þis tyme of grace/ is of more perfeccioun&meper; per|vertu of þe sacramentis/ and fredom of þe gospel&meper; þan was Moises|lawe/ and þou a more perfite man&meper; in keping þis perfeccioun &Verbar;|But & þou be apostataa&meper; in breking of Goddis heestis/ þanne is|þi peyne so miche þe more&meper; as Poul seide to þe Romayns/ Ro. xi o ./|'Tu autem fide stas. noli altum sapere sed time/ si enim deus|naturalibus ramis non pepercit. ne forte nec tibi parcat' Vulg. Rom. xi. 20, 21. &Verbar;  Þat|is to seie.  Forsoþe þou stondist in þe feiþ&meper; nyle þou be proude/|ne bere þee neuere þe hi&yogh;er&meper; but abide þou mekeli/ in þe holi|drede of þe Lord &Verbar;  Forsoþe siþen þat God sparid not. to þe | kyndli braunchis/ þat is to þe Iewis&meper; þat | he chase to be hise|kyndeli heiris/ Bi war lest bi happe he spare not þee&meper; þat camest|out of þe heeþen stokke/ & arte plauntid in bi grace&meper; of Crist|& hise gospel W. V. 'Forsoth thou stondist by feith.  Nyle thou sauere hi&yogh;e thing, but|drede thou, forsothe if God sparide not the kyndely braunchis, lest peraventure|he spare not thee.' &Verbar;  Se now þyn apostasie&meper; þou vnkynde wrecche/|& þe falsenes þat þou vsest&meper; a&yogh;en Cristis gospel/  Mat. xxi o .|Mar. ix o . Luk. xix o . & Ion. ii o ./ 'Intrauit Iesu in templum dei.|& eiciebat omnes vendentes & ementes in templo & mensas nummulariorum|& cathedras vendencium columbas euertit' Vulg. Matt. xxi. 12; Luc. xix. 45; Joh. ii. 15. &Verbar; Þat is to seie.|Iesu entrid in to þe temple of God&meper; & he cast out alle sellars &|biears in þe temple&meper; & þe bordis of mony-makears/ & he turned|vp-so-doun&meper; þe chaiers of hem þat soolden dowues/ and he seide|vnto hem&meper; it is writen Isaye .lvi o . Vulg. Isaias lvi. 7. my hous schal be clepid. an|hous MS. hou. of preiour/ forsoþe &yogh;e han made it a den of þeeues W. V. 'Jhesus entride in to the temple of God, and kest out of the|temple alle sellynge and biynge; and he turnyde upsodoun the bordis of|chaungeris, and the chaiers of men sellynge culveris.  And he seith to hem It|is writen, My hous shal be clepid an hous of priere; forsothe &yogh;e han made it|a denne of thefes.' &Verbar; Criste|forbediþ þe laite&meper; þe vsing of her marchaundise/ eiþir in toune|or in chirche&meper; on her holy dai/ & he dampneþ more strei&yogh;tlier&meper; | among þise visiouse prestis/ biyng of her beneficis&meper; & | selling of|her sacramentis/ as doctour Odo seiþ&meper; vpon þis same gospel/|'Columbas vendentes sunt qui spiritualia vendunt | & si non|clamant ore. tum cum iuda dicunt/  Quid uultis dare&meper; & ego
 |vobis eum MS. &emacr;&amacr;. tradam?  Sic clamant monachi ceterique religiosi&meper;|habitum & suffragia vendentes. item non sacerdotes diuina celebrantes|& tales in ecclesia dei multiplicantur? vbi credis quod sit|domus orationis. ibi invenies speluncam latronum/ omnes qui|non intrant per hostium id est christum. sed per pecuniam uel|seculi gratiam fures sunt & latrones per murum fractum ingredientes/|quia murus ecclesie rumpitur cum prece uel precio aut|sanguine minus ydoneus ad beneficium ecclesiasticum indigne promoueatur' Odo of Cheriton, Flores Sermonum , fols. cvi, cvii. /|Hec ille &Verbar;  Þat is to seie. þei ben sellers of dowues&meper;|þat spirituel þingis sellen/ & þou&yogh; þei crien not wiþ her mouþe&meper;|neþles MS. neþels. þei seyn wiþ Iudas/ what wole &yogh;e &yogh;yue&meper; & I schal bitraie|him to &yogh;ou? Þus crien mounkis&meper; & oþir bastard religioun/ þat|sellen as þei mai take þerfore&meper; her habit & her suffragijs/ & oþir|prestis don | als wick&meper; þat treten diuine seruice/ & suche ben |now multiplied&meper; in þe chirche of God/ þerfore where as þou|wenest&meper; þat is þe hous of preiour/ þere schalt þou redili fynde&meper;|a den of mani þeues/ forsoþe alle þat entren not&meper; bi þe door|þat is Crist/ but bi money or seculere fauour&meper; þei ben ni&yogh;tþeues|& dai-þeues/ þat entren in bi a broken wowe&meper; vnwiting|Iesu Crist/ for he proueþ not her dedis&meper; & þat is his vnknowyng/|for þanne is þe chirche wowe&meper; al to-broken doun/ whanne þe|vnable is avaunsid&meper; to þe chirches benefice/ eiþir for preiour or|for pris&meper; or for vndwe seruice &Verbar; Siþen oure Lord Iesu Crist&meper; seide to his apostlis/ þat oone of|hem was a deuel&meper; & ment it bi Iudas/ Be not þise apostataas&meper; þat|don als yuel as he/ worþi to be clepid deuelis&meper; bi þe same resoun?|Þei ben greet questioners&meper; & askars of þe lawe/ but þei wole not|do so miche&meper; as putt þerto her fynger/ & þei heepen charge on|oþir&meper; more þan þei mai bere/ Þei ben preisars of seintis&meper; & no|þing her folowars/ þei ben heerars | of þe lawe&meper; but no þing þe |doars/ þei ben alwey lernyng&meper; & neuir þei wole be perfite/ þus þei|boosten in þe lawe&meper; wiþ worschip & wiþ wynnyng/ but bi breking|of þe lawe&meper; þei don dispise her God &Verbar;

12.10:
Þe nynþe heeste &Verbar; The nynþe comaundement of God is þis. Exo. xx o . Deuto. v o .|'Non concupisces domum proximi tui' Vulg. Ex. xx. 17. / Þou schalt not coueite þe|hous of þi neibour &Verbar;  In þe seuenþe heest God forbediþ&meper; þe vnleful|takyng of oþir mennes goodis/ & so in þat he refreyneþ&meper; þe vnskilfulnes|of mannes dede/ |  But in þis heest God forbediþ&meper; þe |coueitise of vnleful taking/ & in þat he refreyneþ&meper; þe vnordinat|appetite of mannes desire/ namli in alle þo þingis&meper; þat ben|vnmoveable/ þat is to seie. þat moun not move hem silf&meper; bi her|owene my&yogh;t from oo place to anoþir/ as ben hous. lond. gold. &|suche oþir like to þise &Verbar; And þis viciouse coueitise&meper; if it be conteyned/ growiþ to deeþ|of þe soule&meper; from þe roote of mannes herte/ for whanne þe wille|haþ consentid&meper; to do þat þing þat God forbediþ/ þou&yogh; þe dede|folowe not aftir&meper; in outward si&yogh;t of mannes doome/ & no þing|lettiþ to do þe dede&meper; saue wille mai not as it wolde/ þanne þe|soule is deed goostli&meper; wiþynne þe hous of þe bodi/ And þis deeþ|is signified&meper; bi a persoones dou&yogh;tir/ þat was deed wiþynne hir|fadris hous&meper; & Crist bi myracle &yogh;aue hir lijf/ Mat. ix o ./ Mar. v o .|Luk. viii o . Vulg. Matt. ix. 18-26; Marc. v. 22-43; Luc. viii. 41-56. Summe norischen her coueitise&meper; til it spring vnto a dede/ as a|careyn opunly deed&meper; þat lieþ bi þe weye enfecting þe peple/ and|þis is tau&yogh;t in þe widouse sone&meper; þat was born deed on a beere/ wiþouten þe &yogh;atis of þe | citee&meper; for to putt him in his graue/|Luk. vii o Vulg. Luc. vii. 11-15. / Crist rerid him bi his myracle&meper; & &yogh;aue him a&yogh;en to his|modir &Verbar; Summe feeden her foule coueitise&meper; wiþ lust & lykyng & delectacioun/|in þou&yogh;t. in worde. & in werke&meper; & þis is moost abhomynable/|for it was schewid in Lazarus/ Ion. xi o . Vulg. Joh. xi. 1-46. þat lay deed foure|daies in his graue/ & Crist bi miracle to turne þe Iewis&meper; rerid vp|his bodi & &yogh;aue it þe spirit &Verbar; Alle þise þre ben a&yogh;enst þis heest of God/ & ben worþi eendles|peyne&meper; but if God þoru&yogh; his graciouse mercy/ move hem to vertu|& to verry penaunce&meper; þat ben deed in þise forseid foule coueitises/|Þat is to seie. in coueitise of herte&meper; of dede. & of custum/ and|þerfore þe wise man. Ecc. xviii o . 'Post concupiscencias tuas non|eas' Vulg. Ecclesiasticus xviii. 30. / Go þou not awey fro þi God&meper; aftir þin owene couetises W. V. 'After thi lustis go thou not.' 1388, 'Go thou not aftir thi|coueitises.' &Verbar;|Lord hou schulde he kepe him from a viciouse dede&meper; þat doiþ not|out of his herte. þe coueitise þerof? Certis it is as vnposible&meper; as to|saue þat hous from brennyng/ þat þou settist on fire&meper; wiþ þin | owene handis &Verbar;  A weede may not be distried&meper; but | if þat|delictable coueitise of synne. be pullid out of þe herte/ for if þere|abide ony part of þis foule couetise&meper; vndrawen vp in þe herte/|anoon aftir comeþ þerof. þeeft. false purchase&meper; & suche oþir/ and|þerfor seide Moyses&meper; vnto þe children of Israel/ Deuto. xix o ./|'Non assumes & transferes terminos proximi tui quos fixerunt|priores tui in possessione tua quam dominus deus tuus dabit tibi' Vulg. Deut. xix. 14. &Verbar;|Þat is to seie. þou schalt not take. ne þou schalt not passe þe termes|or þe boundes of þi nei&yogh;bore&meper; þe whiche þin elderis han sett/ in þe|whiche possessioun&meper; þat þe Lord þi God schal &yogh;yue to þee W. V. 'Thou shalt not take, and ouerbere the teermes of thi nei&yogh;bour,|the whiche han maad rather men in thi possessioun, that the Lord thi God|shal &yogh;yue to thee.'  1388, 'Thou schalt not take, and turne over the termes of|thi nei&yogh;bore, which the formere men settiden in thi possessioun, which thi|Lord God schal &yogh;yue to thee.' / For|who þat takiþ awey his nei&yogh;boris grounde&meper; þat is to seie. lond or|place. wood or watir. corn or grasse. in felde or in toune. þoru&yogh; ony|of þise forseide couetises&meper; he stondiþ in þat acursid of God & his
 |lawe/ for þus it is writen.  Deuto. xxvii o ./ 'Maledictus qui transfert|terminos proximi sui' Vulg. Deut. xxvii. 17. / Cursid be þat man or womman. þat|passiþ þe boundis of laweful mesure&meper; bitwene her nei&yogh;bours &|hem W. V. 'Cursid that overberith the teermes of his nei&yogh;bore.' / A&yogh;en þis comaundement&meper; þe fende wiþ hise cau-|-tels/ haþ largid |þis couetise&meper; to alle þre astatis/ þat vnneþ ony man. takiþ ony|hede&meper; hou þat he cum bi good. so þat he were riche &Verbar; Comunes han purchasid&meper; at anticristis procatour/ to be fermours|of þe chirche&meper; for couetise of wynnyng/ and bi þis parischens&meper;|ben brou&yogh;t in many custumes/ þat stroyen pees & norischen baate&meper;|& quenchen Goddis lawe/  But who þat euere seiþ or biddiþ&meper;|biside Goddis wille/ þat is not proued in holy writ&meper; & opunli|declarid/ he is a false witnesar&meper; & doiþ cursid sacrilege/ and so|seiþ seint Austin/ 'Cum dominus dixit in euangelio. ego sum|veritas. & non dixit ego sum consuetudo. itaque veritate manifestata|veritati cedat consuetudo/  Petrus qui circumsidebat cessit Paulo|veritatem predicanti/ ergo cum christus veritas sit magis veritatem|quam consuetudinem sequi debemus quia consuetudinem racio &|veritas semper excludunt' Augustinus, De Baptismo contra Donatistas , Lib. III, cap. vi-ix|(Migne, tom. 43, cols. 143, 144); Gratian, Decreti Pars Prima, dist. viii,|cap. vi (Migne, tom. 187, cols. 46, 47). / whanne þe Lord God haþ seid in his|gospel. I am trouþe. & he seid not. I am custum&meper; þanne whanne|trouþe is schewid. custum mut nede &yogh;yue stede to trouþe/ Petir|þat circumcidid. consentid to Poul. preching þe trouþe/ þerfor|siþen | Crist is trouþe&meper; we owen miche more to swe trouþe þan |custum/ for euer-more resoun & trouþe&meper; schullen exclude custum/|and whanne resoun & trouþe. excluden þise fermours. & alle her|false custumes&meper; he is a verry membre of þe deuel. þat maynteneþ|þe contrarie/ & makiþ þe hous of Iesu Crist&meper; þe comune schopp|of marchaundise &Verbar; But lordis here ben more to blame&meper; þat schulde chastise þis|synne/ for summe ben fermours hem silf&meper; & fauouren for couetise/|þat þe persun schal haue leue&meper; to liee in grooti placis/ as an|hogge in þe myre&meper; & leeue his cure vnkept &Verbar;  &yogh;he lordis in þise|daies&meper; ben so smyten wiþ couetise/ þat þei holden false gooten
 |goodis&meper; a&yogh;ens her owene conscience/ and feele siþes reren strong|hand&meper; armyd in wickidnes/ to kille men boþe sleping & wakyng&meper;|to encrese her lordschipis &Verbar;  Kyng Acab for couetise&meper; of Nabathis|vyn&yogh;erde/ þat he desirid for to haue had&meper; a&yogh;en þis kny&yogh;tis wille/ | leide him gronyng on his bedde&meper; & wolde taste | no mete/ for|Nabath seide he wolde not chaunge&meper; ne selle his kynde eritage &Verbar;|But Iezabel þat wickid quene&meper; &yogh;aue þe kyng suche counseile/ þat|þei kesten þis manes deeþ&meper; bi a fals sclaundir/ & þus þei brou&yogh;ten|him to an eende&meper; & reioyced his vyn&yogh;erde &Verbar;  God sent worde to|Acab & to Iezabel&meper; bi þe prophet Hely/ þat for þei hadden do|þus coueitouseli&meper; a&yogh;ens his comaundement/ her blood schulde be|schadde on þe erþe&meper; & houndis schulde lik it/  And moreouere.|God took veniaunce&meper; for þis greuouse synne/ vpon þe seed þat|cam of hem&meper; in to þe þridde & þe fourþe generacioun/  And if|þat we tooke hede&meper; hou lordis han slayn iche oþir/ in scheding|her blood in þe felde&meper; for coueitise of lording/ we schulde not|woundir þou&yogh; Goddis hand&meper; be strecchid ouere hise peple/ to|smyt wiþ veniaunce as he doiþ&meper; & no man may avoide it/ and if|þou wilt wite&meper; what is þis veniaunce/ God seiþ bi þe prophete. | Ose. iiii o /  Þat his veniaunce is&meper; whanne he | wiþdrawiþ his|chastising. & þe &yogh;erde of amending/ and suffriþ hise enemyes to|regne in her synne&meper; to her deeþ day/ & aftir to dampne hem bodi|& soule&meper; euer wiþouten eende/  And to þis acordiþ Gregory&meper; in|hise morals vpon Iob/ 'Deus quibusdam hec parcit&meper; vt in eternum|feriat' &Verbar;  Þat is to se. In þis lijf to summe God spariþ&meper; þat he|may smyte hem wiþouten ende/ and Iob seiþ. xxi o . 'Quare impij|viuunt subleuati sunt confortatique diuiciis/ semen eorum permanet|coram eis propinquorum turba & nepotum in conspectu eorum domus|eorum secure sunt & pacate & non est virga dei super illos/ Bos eorum|concepit & non abhortiuit/ vacca peperit & non est priuata fetu|suo &Verbar;  Egrediuntur quasi greges paruuli eorum & infantes eorum|exultant MS. exultauit. lusibus/ tenent timpanum & cytharam & gaudent ad|sonitum organi/  Ducunt in bonis dies suos&meper; & in puncto ad|inferna descendunt' Vulg. Job xxi. 7-13. &Verbar;  Þat is to seie. whi lyuen wickid men|avauncid & counfortid in richessis? þe seed of hem dwelliþ biforn | hem&meper; & þe company of ny&yogh; | frendis & cosynes in her si&yogh;t/ her|housis ben siker. & þe &yogh;eerde of God. þat is clepid his chastising&meper;
